swap(uint256,address,address,uint256).details: This function is safeguarded from re-entrancy attacks by the nonReentrant modifier.

params.amountIn: Quantity of the input token to be swapped.
params.poolIdx: The index of the pool selected for the swap.
params.recipient: Address designated to receive the swapped tokens.
params.tokenIn: Token to be given as input for the swap.

returns.amountOut: The amount of tokens the recipient obtains.

swap(uint256,address,address,uint256,add.details: This function is protected against re-entrancy attacks by the nonReentrant modifier.

params.amountIn: Amount of the input token to be swapped.
params.poolIdx: The index of the pool utilized for the swap.
params.recipient: Address that will receive the swapped tokens.
params.routingAgent: Address of the routingAgent contract used for the swap.
params.tokenIn: Token to be provided as input for the swap.

returns.amountOut: The amount of tokens the recipient will receive.

swap(uint256,address,address,uint256).notice: Conducts a token swap with the resulting tokens allocated to the development fund.

swap(uint256,address,address,uint256,add.notice: Performs a token swap using a specified routingAgent.
